Pastor Ivan Waldeck says since Rashied Staggie changed his life, all he wanted was to bring gangs together and motivate them to take a different life path. CAPE TOWN - Pastor Ivan Waldeck says he doesn't know who would want Rashied Staggie dead. He says since the former gang leader changed his life, all he wanted was to bring gangs together and motivate them to take a different life path. READ: Police can't confirm Mitchells Plain murder linked to that of Staggie "According to me, Rahied Staggie, as I worked with him more than 20 years after he changed his life and become a reborn christian, I don't know that he has an enemy. Rashied after changing his life he wanted to bring all of them together," said Pastor Waldeck. Staggie was shot on Friday in front of his home in Salt River, Cape Town. 